<image 1> What does the shaded area represent? P(___< x < ___)

A. 5,6
B. 5,7
C. 6,7
D. 6,8

The shaded area in the graph represents the probability that the random variable \( x \) falls within a specific range. The shaded region is between the values 6 and 7 on the x-axis.

Therefore, the shaded area represents \( P(6 < x < 7) \).

The correct choice is:

\boxed{C}
